# To Issues Workflow

## When to Use

- A PRD Issue exists and needs to be broken into Slice Issues.
- The user asks to decompose a PRD, create implementation tickets, or break down a planned feature.
- Preparing work for `yarn dispatch-agents`.

## Core Approach

Read and follow `.github/skills/to-issues/SKILL.md` exactly.

Key points:
- Ask the user for the PRD Issue number if not already provided.
- Fetch the PRD Issue body via `gh issue view <N>` — never work from memory.
- Each slice must be a thin vertical slice through all layers (schema → API → UI → tests).
- Every slice body must start with `PRD: #<parent-issue-number>` — required by `dispatch-agents`.
- Flag `type:hitl` slices with ⚠️ in the quiz — they will be skipped by `dispatch-agents`.
- Publish issues in dependency order; update PRD `## Slices` section afterwards.
- Run `yarn ai:create-labels` first if any required labels are missing.

## Next Step

After slices are published, run `yarn dispatch-agents --prd <issue-number>` to hand off AFK slices to autonomous agents.

## Skill Files

- `.github/skills/to-issues/SKILL.md` — full skill definition
- `.github/skills/to-issues/config.md` — label vocabulary and issue formats
